                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.852/63</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Telephone Conversation, by the Chief of the
                        Division of the American Republics</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                    >Duggan</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-22">December 22,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Pierre Boal, Counselor of the Embassy in Mexico City, stated that Señor
                    Fernandez del Castillo had informed him that he had sounded out the German
                    Minister with regard to the purchase of the seven German ships still remaining
                    in Mexican waters. The German Minister was said to have replied that if a “fair
                    offer” were made, it would probably be accepted.</p>
            </div>
